				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Abiotic Depletion Potential (ADP) is a method used in Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) to analyze the impact of an object on the world around it. It is the most widely accepted LCIA method. However, it has limitations such as neglecting resources that can be recycled. Depletion of abiotic resources is a disputed impact category in LCA due to different problem definitions and choices regarding parameters and data. The LCA results identified abiotic depletion potential for fossil fuels (ADPF) as key impact indicators.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">非生物耗竭潜能值 （ADP） 是一种用于生命周期评估 （LCA） 的方法，用于分析物体对其周围世界的影响。它是最广泛接受的LCIA方法。但是，它有局限性，例如忽略了可以回收的资源。非生物资源的枯竭是 LCA 中一个有争议的影响类别，因为关于参数和数据的问题定义和选择不同。LCA结果将化石燃料的非生物枯竭潜力（ADPF）确定为关键影响指标。</common:generalComment>
